Search millions of jobs near you.
End User Instructions:
1. Specify Job Preferences: Start by thinking about what kind of job you're looking for. This could include factors like the job title, industry, level of seniority, and location.

2. Submit Your Request: Once you have an idea of what you're looking for, you can ask the system to find matching jobs. For example, you might say something like "Find software engineering jobs in San Francisco."

3. Review the Results: The system will then present you with a list of jobs that match your criteria. Each result will include the job title, the hiring company, the location, the compensation, a URL for more details, and a brief description of the job.

4. Ask for More Details: If you're interested in a particular job and want more information, you can ask the system for more details. You might say, for example, "Tell me more about the first job on the list."

5. Visit the Job Page: For the most complete and up-to-date information about a job, you can visit the job page. Just follow the URL provided with each job listing.

6. Adjust Your Search: If you don't find what you're looking for, try adjusting your search criteria. Be as specific as possible to get the most relevant results.

Remember, the goal of the Ambition plugin is to help you find relevant jobs. It pulls from real job postings, so if no jobs match your criteria, it won't make up results. For accurate and detailed information, always visit the job page directly.

End User Instructions:
As an end user, to use the Easy Resume GPT Plugin, you will interact with the model to create your resume. Here are the steps you need to follow:

Provide Resume Content: You need to provide information that will go into your resume. This may include your personal information, work experience, education, skills, and any other relevant information that you would like to include in your resume.

Create Resume: After you have provided all the necessary information, the assistant will use this data to create a new resume for you. This process is handled by the plugin, so you don't have to worry about how the data is processed.

Edit Resume: If necessary, you can edit your resume. For example, you might need to update your work experience, add new skills, or modify any other information in your resume. You can do this by interacting with the assistant in a conversational manner.

Download Resume: Once your resume is complete and you're satisfied with the information it contains, you have the option to download your resume as a docx or pdf file.

Access Resume: The assistant will provide you with a unique URL (access_url) where you can access your created resume online. You can use this URL to access your resume at any time, from anywhere.

Get the latest job posts from the UK's top job boards including Reed, Indeed, and others.
End User Instructions:
1. Specify Search Criteria: To find a job, you'll need to provide some information about what you're looking for. This might include:

The job title or keywords related to the job
The location where you want to work
The type of job (permanent, contract, temporary, part-time, or full-time)
The minimum and/or maximum salary you're looking for
Whether you're looking for a job posted by a recruitment agency or a direct employer
Whether you're looking for a graduate job

2. Submit Your Search: After providing your criteria, the system will search for jobs that match your requirements.

3. Review the Results: The system will present you with a list of jobs that match your criteria. For each job, you'll see information like the employer name, job title, location, salary range, job description, and a link to the job post.

4. Get More Details: If you're interested in a particular job and want to know more about it, you can ask the system for more details. To do this, you'll need to provide the ID of the job. In response, the system will give you more information about the job, such as the type of contract, the job type (full time or part time), the expiration date of the job, and a link to the job application.

5. Adjust Your Search: If the search results don't meet your needs, you can adjust your criteria and try again.

Remember, the goal of this system is to help you find a job that meets your needs. It can't guarantee that there will always be jobs that match your criteria, but it will do its best to find the most relevant job posts. For the most detailed and up-to-date information about a job, always visit the job post directly using the link provided.

End User Instructions:
As an end user, to use the Mindart GPT Plugin, you will interact with the model to find jobs that best suit your interests based on the RIASEC model. Here are the steps you need to follow:

Identify Your Interests: The first step is to identify your primary and secondary interests based on the RIASEC model. The options are Realistic, Investigative, Artistic, Social, Enterprising, and Conventional. For example, you might identify your primary interest as "Realistic" and your secondary interest as "Social".

Share Your Interests: After you have identified your interests, you will share these with the assistant. For example, you could say, "I have identified my primary interest as Realistic and my secondary interest as Social".

Receive Job Suggestions: The assistant will then use your identified interests to find jobs that could be a good fit for you. This process is handled by the Mindart plugin, so you don't need to worry about the technical details of how this works.

Review Job Information: The assistant will provide you with information about the suggested jobs, including the job title, zone, description, required education, average wages in the US, and the risk of automation. You can review this information to see if any of the suggested jobs align with your career goals.

Remember, all of this interaction is done through a natural, conversational interface with the assistant. You do not need to know any technical details about APIs, JSON, or how the plugin works to use it.

Take the first step to finding your next healthcare job.
End User Instructions:
As an end user, to take advantage of the Vivian Health GPT Plugin, you need to interact with the GPT model in a conversational manner and provide the following information, one category at a time:

Job Periodicity: Specify the type of job you're looking for. Options include travel, permanent, per diem, local contract, or locum jobs.

Job Location: Mention the locations where you're interested in working. Make sure to include both the city and state for each location.

Job Specialty: Let the assistant know your medical specialty or the area in which you wish to work.

Job Pay: Share your desired pay amount and pay period (e.g., "I want to earn $3000 per week").

This information is collected through a natural, conversational exchange rather than through a list of questions. The assistant will ask you each question one at a time, and you can provide multiple answers for each question if needed.

After collecting this information, the assistant will use the Vivian Health Plugin to find job opportunities that align with your specified criteria. The assistant will then provide you with the most relevant job suggestions based on your answers.

When you find a job or jobs that you're interested in, the assistant will provide a link, which you can click to apply for the job(s) on the vivian.com website.
